    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.24"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Sunday Afternoon April 20, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Neihardts:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was such a beautiful service this afternoon &#8212; just the way she wanted it &#8212; "No sadness of Farewell." She was there, listening and watching when Dr. Neihardt read the poem and the Easter, and when Sigurd played for her, and Hilda sang, and all her loved ones were close around her,&#8212;husband and children and grandchildren and friends. I have never witnessed a more impressive service</p>
                
                <p>My dearest love and admiration for all of you. God bless you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lura Lewis</signed>
                    <address><addrLine>211 Edgewood</addrLine></address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
